         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Br. Consulate Jerusalem Octr 20/60 ¶ My dear Mueller ¶  ¶ The address of this will surprise you I dare say, but I have taken advantage of my 6 weeks leave ¶  to visit Syria, &amp; have come here en route ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">60.10.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Br. Consulate Jerusalem Octr 20/60</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The address of this will surprise you I dare say, but I have taken advantage of my 6 weeks leave<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hooker was actually away for ten weeks, leaving England around 9 September 1860, departing from Trieste on 15 September and returning to London on 17 November.</p>
               </note> to visit Syria, &amp; have come here en route to Nazareth &amp;c &amp; so home by Caipha<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Haifa.</p>
               </note> &amp; Beirut. I have already been through N. Syria, crossing the Lebanon &amp; Antilebanon to Damascus. The season is absolutely <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">dead</hi>
               </seg> as far as regards Vegetation, but I have been greatly interested in various ways. My chief object in writing now is to ask your aid towards improving this interesting locality by an envoi of Australian seeds. Mr &amp; Mrs Finn the Consul &amp; his lady are making great efforts to introduce trees especially around Jerusalem have purchased land &amp; gone to a great deal of expence &amp; trouble, the soil &amp; climate are admirable &amp; the country is cursed by man &amp; man's works alone — I believe that many Victoria trees would succeed here better than those of any other country, &amp; I know that you would be proud to be the instrument of populating the country with arborescent vegetation<seg>.</seg> no one could do it so well as you &amp; no plants would succeed better than Australian. The quick-growing ones would be the most important as shade &amp; a break-wind of plants that will withstand drought are the first requisites — We can send from Kew Californian, Cape &amp; N.W. Indian seeds &amp; shall do so, but you can cut us out [by<seg>]</seg> Victorian — The following would be especially desirable.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Blue Gum</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Peppermint do</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Various <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>s</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Casuarina">Casuarina</name>s</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Callitris">Callitris</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Melaleuca">Melaleuca</name>s</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Anthesteria">Anthesteria</name> &amp; other dry climate large Grasses.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Pomaderris">Pomaderris</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Banksia">Banksia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Hakea">Hakea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Grevillea">Grevillea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c &amp;c &amp;c You can from the above hint, judge better than I can indicate, what would be acceptable.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Address the packet</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Finn Eqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>British Consul</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jerusalem</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Care of the British Consul</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Alexandria</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I go home by the November mail</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever sincerely yrs</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos. D Hooker.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to J. Moore, 15 January 1862, and Rosen (1991).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Please put on each packet whether tree, shrub, or grass. This is more important than the Scientific names</p>
